question: One word prompt: disgrace
answer:
“You’re a disgrace.” 

The smooth stone felt warm against Beau’s cheek, slick with the sweat of the combatants. Trembling fingers pressed against the tiles, she tongued one of her teeth and felt it shift. The hot trickle of blood against the back of her throat hinted at a possible broken nose. 

Her heart pounded in her ears, making her face flush and pulse with burning pressure. Zeenoth’s words echoed in her mind, round and round, blocking out all other sounds until it was just her and the seeds of doubt. 

She suddenly envisioned her father standing over her, voice low with barely contained resentment as he banned yet another toy, or book, or activity. In all those years, his face had never betrayed any disappointment. 

No, that meant there had to have been expectations. 

Beau pushed up against the tiles and stood tall, wiping away the blood from her lip. 

You’re a disgrace. 

She spit on the ground, held up her fists and grinned; 

“Good.”

title: Nott the Halfling
body:
Anyone else imagining the gang being level 9 and Nott dying and before she died she was talking to Caleb or Beau or Jester or the crew as a whole about how much she hates being a goblin how the skin just feels so so wrong on her and she wants to change. And right after she died Caduceus is getting ready to start Revivify but Caleb stops him. Nila is nearby, she should be able to bring her back and possibly not as a goblin. We have time. And they go and it’s a bit more expensive but worth it. She has to wait until the next day to prepare it but she is willing.

Then the next day while she casts the spell one of the offerings is Caleb coming up and going Nott we know you hated being a goblin, we can’t promise you will come back as you see yourself but there is a good, though not guaranteed chance you won’t come back as a goblin. So please come back as however you do and I promise that no matter what you come back as I will do my best to bring you as you view yourself. I just hope that you come back so you can live as not a goblin as you have wished.

Then Matt roles a number between 61 and 76 (or equivalent if using a different table to include more races).

summary: Hello Bee <3 I felt like drawing some proper Critical Role fanart. I love all of the Mighty Nein characters, but Jester reminds...
caption:
Hello Bee <3

I felt like drawing some proper Critical Role fanart.

I love all of the Mighty Nein characters, but Jester reminds me a lot of myself as a child. I was often alone but rarely lonely. Jester had the Traveler, I had my imagination. There was however always a slowly growing sadness inside, which I’ve had to deal with over the years. I hope Jester finds her happy future, as I’m trying to!
